Description:
Ready for you to call home...
Located on the 31st floor of the popular 'Victoria Point' residential complex in the ever-vibrant Victoria Harbour precinct of Docklands is this spacious and vacant two bedroom apartment featuring an amazing floor plan allowing every room in this home to face the Harbour for breathtaking water views by day or night!
Luxurious features include:
- Two large bedrooms with built-in robes,
- Well equipped central kitchen with integrated stainless steel appliances and stone bench tops,
- Spacious living area with floor to ceiling windows for 'wide screen' views of marina,
- An adjoining balcony perfect for entertainment or as a relaxing retreat,
- Closed off laundry area,
- One undercover car space and storage cage,
- Ducted air conditioning and heating,
- Concierge.
Positioned just a stone's throw to local waterfront cafes and restaurants, Etihad Stadium, Southern Cross Station, and free trams literally at your doorstep, what more could you possibly need?
Don't miss out on the golden opportunity to secure this superb apartment ready for you to move in straight away! Great value, great location and fabulous living!
Call Peter Doan now on 0423 399 999 for an inspection.

Description:
Stylish Victoria Point Living is a Must See!
Graced with an amazing amount of living space matched by memorable Victoria Point style and views of Docklands Park, Port Phillip Bay, and the city skyline, this 17th floor two bedroom apartment is a sensational opportunity in the Victoria Harbour precinct. Love the location close to Etihad Stadium, The Hub @ Docklands, Bourke Street eateries, trams and Southern Cross Station.
Accommodation: All types of buyers are sure to embrace this amazing and generous apartment, which offers floor-to-ceiling windows, quality stone benchtops, and premium fittings and fixtures. Major highlights include a huge lounge and dining zone, undercover balcony with brilliant views, gourmet kitchen offering premium stainless steel appliances as well as a handy island bench, master bedroom with private ensuite and dual built-in robes, 2nd bedroom with BIRs, and a central bathroom with laundry.

Description:
Stylish, Relaxed, and Boasting Gorgeous Harbour Views!
Enjoying fantastic open plan living on the 8th floor of the Quays residential complex, this two bedroom Docklands apartment is well-presented, stylish, and will be a relaxed place to call home for one lucky buyer.
The generous central living zone has the bonus of enjoying designated tiled meals and carpeted lounge areas, with the meals area adjoined by a fully-equipped stone kitchen graced with a glass splashback and premium stainless steel appliances.
The balcony with excellent Victoria Harbour vistas can be accessed via the lounge as well as the master bedroom which boasts an ensuite, while the 2nd bedroom with BIR sits next to the central bathroom with European laundry. Reverse cycle cooling, intercom, secure car space, and access to the pool, spa, gym, tennis court, yoga centre, cinema, and rooftop garden are other features.
Near Harbour Town Shopping Centre, Etihad Stadium, NewQuay Promenade, trams, and Southern Cross Station.

Description:
Luxury, unique with fantastic views
Feel part of the action from your own private terrace while enjoying spectacular city view and the sun setting over the Bolte bridge! Split over two generous levels and the epitome of luxurious and extravagant waterside living, this 3 bedroom, 2.5 bathroom apartment is an exquisite Nolan Tower offering with stunning space both inside and out!
The unique duel level offering features a ground floor with an expansive lounge, private marina views and dining leading out to a private balcony, while a sleek stone kitchen with stainless steel appliances sits right next to the handy powder room.
Upstairs is dominated by three bedrooms including the magnificent master retreat with a WIR and spa ensuite, while a great sized wraparound entertainer’s or family terrace (with access to building pool), as well as 2 more balconies, is bliss for alfresco meals as you enjoy the city and marina views. A central bathroom, Euro laundry, ducted heat/cool throughout, storage cage, and the enviable benefit of 2 car spaces on the same level as the apartment.
You can also access heated pool and gym and are moments to amazing attractions & transport.

Description:
Awe-Inspiring Docklands Living in The Arkley
Feel right at home in one of the Docklands best buildings as you enjoy the modern style and brilliant views that accompany this two bedroom apartment. In the superb Arkley complex and superb for owner-occupiers, this property in the lively NewQuay precinct is moments to Harbour Town Shopping Centre, Costco, Etihad Stadium, Victoria Harbour, free trams, and Southern Cross Station.
Accommodation: With access to outstanding facilities including an outdoor pool, gymnasium, golf practice net, and spa, this impressive 7th floor abode offers up bright lounge and dining which flows out to the undercover balcony with great marina views, kitchen with stainless steel appliances plus a full window allowing for views of the Melbourne Star Observation Wheel, both bedrooms with views as well as mirrored built-in robes, and a stylish bathroom with separate powder room. The building is named after notable Australian artist Howard Arkley and is designed by renowned architect Fender Kastalidis, as well as featuring artwork at the entry and in the lobby.
Features: Secure car space, Storage Cage, European laundry, reverse cycle heating and cooling, secure intercom entry.

Perfect Park Views
This brilliant apartment is located in The Montage residential complex next to beautiful parklands, a rarity for inner city living, you're able to enjoy the Marina at your doorstep, the CBD a tram ride away and an array of entertainment at your leisure!
Features include:
- A bright and spacious open plan living area,
- Galley style kitchen with ample bench space and stainless steel appliances,
- Stunning views of the park towards the city from the balcony,

The Montage building is a boutique development set in a great location being close to the Woolworths, South Wharf DFO, Southern Cross Station, the free tram zone, Etihad Stadium and a vast range of cafes and restaurants.

Description:
SUPERB DOCKLANDS HOME WITH BREATHTAKING VIEWS
Overlooking Victoria Harbour on the 19th floor of the Arkley Complex is this magnificent, light filled, corner apartment showcasing breathtaking views with an intelligent floor plan.
Offering an open-plan living, dining, and kitchen, this contemporary 3 bedroom home is built for entertaining. The entrance hall flows into the living zone and out onto the balcony, which presents an awe-inspiring panorama of Victoria Harbour, the Yarra River, Port Melbourne and Port Philip Bay – perfect for enjoying a cold drink after a long day. The recently renovated kitchen features stone-bench tops, new stainless steel appliances, and plenty of storage in the stylish cupboards and drawers. Imagine cooking up a storm in your new kitchen whilst taking in the dazzling display of the Iconic Melbourne Star.
The master bedroom is generous in size for apartment living, featuring views to the north, a newly renovated walk-in-robe, and a stylish ensuite with a clean, modern finish. The second bedroom is also generous in size, with a large floor to ceiling wardrobe, and offers great views to the north of the Melbourne Star and Mount Macedon. The third bedroom is also decent in size, with a built in robe, and works perfectly as a guest/child's room or study. Rounding out this chic Docklands home is a central bathroom, complete with separate shower and bath, as well as a powder room, and laundry room
Central heating & cooling, 2 secure side by side car spaces, ground level storage cage, and secure swipe & intercom entry complete this smart inner city pad. Including use of the heated swimming pool, spa, gymnasium, golf practice net, and function rooms, this is resort style living 365 days a year.
Conveniently located in the free tram zone, and in the North Melbourne Primary School & University High School zones, and with Etihad Stadium, a world class shopping precinct, and an array of waterside restaurants and bars on your doorstep, this must see apartment is perfectly situated only minutes from the CBD and CityLink.

Description:
Enjoy Convesso Luxury and Stunning Facilities
Located in the stunning Victoria Harbour precinct and an impressive package of open living and contemporary class, this excellent one bedroom apartment in the coveted Convesso building will cater for all types of buyers.
A practical and open floorplan is sure to make everyday living easy and comfortable, while bright floor-to-ceiling windows and quality fittings add to the stylish living experience. A spacious central lounge and meals hub is adjoined by a gorgeous kitchen with a mosaic tiled splashback and stainless steel appliances, meanwhile a sizeable undercover balcony flows out from the living zone and is ideal for alfresco meals.
The bedroom offers built-in robes and easy access to the central bathroom which has a handy European laundry, while other property features include ducted heat/cool, 24-hr concierge, and facilities including a large indoor swimming pool, gym, spa, sauna, sky garden, business centre, cinema, and lounge.
The wonderful Victoria Harbour area is surrounded by a varied mix of residential, office, and retail, and has the highest concentration of green buildings in Australia. This is a perfect opportunity for busy professionals who work nearby or want an easy commute into the CBD, while smart investors will enjoy attractive rental returns on the property.
You’re also literally seconds to the open green space of Buluk Park right on the waterfront, as well as great eateries including Saluministi, Merchant Society, and TAP831. You also have a Woolworths supermarket nearby, as well as the Library at The Dock, Victoria Harbour Promenade, and Etihad Stadium.

Description:
A Jewel in the Crown of Yarra’s Edge
Showcasing unadulterated luxury, unbelievable space both inside and out, and marvellous riverside views that will take your breath away, this two bedroom, two bathroom apartment in the stunning ‘Array’ complex is a Docklands living experience like no other.
With rarely offered 3.6m high ceilings, tall floor-to-ceiling windows, and a Paris colour scheme throughout, this 5th floor retreat ticks all the modern boxes. Expansive central living delivers dedicated lounge and dining areas, with this space flowing out through sliding doors to the spacious balcony where residents can enjoy stunning water and park views.
The state of the art kitchen offers extended bench shelving, unique LED strip lighting, and Miele appliances, meanwhile both bedrooms boast smart BIRs and includes the master retreat featuring a superb ensuite with double headed shower. Other features of this property include central bathroom, European laundry, remote electronic blinds, Sonos sound system, ducted heating and cooling, secure intercom, storage cage, and 2 secure care spaces.
Residents of Array also have access to an on-site gym as well as RekDek which includes a gym, pool, spa, steam room, and sauna.
The Yarra’s Edge precinct is one of the most popular in the area. The nearby South Wharf offers a variety of excellent eateries and bars such as Common Man, Plus 5 Bar, Citizen Café and Bar, and Akachochin, while you’re also near Polly Woodside, Melbourne Exhibition Centre, Crown Entertainment Complex, Etihad Stadium, and Southern Cross Station. You’re also close to the free tram zone which takes you around the city.

Description:
Stunning Space and Amazing Alfresco Entertaining
With unprecedented outdoor space (approx. 60m2) which is bound to make entertaining an undoubted highlight, this sensational two bedroom, two bathroom apartment is a unique and stylish offering in the coveted ‘Arkley’ residential complex.
This residence is a prime prospect for owner-occupiers who love a relaxed indoor/outdoor lifestyle. The alfresco zone at the rear of the property is truly unique and hard to find in apartments, with generous and dedicated patio and courtyard areas making a perfect space to have BBQs with friends or just relax with a quiet wine after work. The plants/tress also benefit from an irrigation system for low maintenance.
Inside, be further impressed by the open plan living and dining zone featuring floor-to-ceiling windows, meanwhile the pristine kitchen adjoining the central area has a long breakfast bar and superior stainless steel appliances. Both bedrooms have BIRs including the spacious main retreat which has room for a study and features direct access to the patio, while two separate bathrooms are well-appointed and modern.
Other property features include a laundry, reverse cycle heating and cooling, secure intercom, secure car space, storage cage and access to a pool, spa, golf practice net, and gym. The impressive building is also named after notable Australian artist Howard Arkley.
The NewQuay precinct is one of the standout areas of the Docklands and a popular choice for residents. You can enjoy an amazing selection of surrounding cafes and restaurants, as well as being close to Costco, Harbour Town Shopping Centre, and an IGA supermarket. You’re also seconds to trams taking you to West Preston, Bundoora RMIT, and the CBD, as well as being near Southern Cross Station.
Insights: 505/20 Rakaia Way, Docklands VIC 3008 was last sold in 2017 and 275 other 2 bedroom unit in Docklands have recently been sold.

Description:
Blissful Docklands Living with Superb Bay Views
With the benefit of awe-inspiring views of Port Phillip Bay from the 30th floor, an open and light-filled floorplan allowing for relaxed living, and two secure car spaces, this impeccable two bedroom apartment in ‘Tower 5’ is a breath of fresh air.
Bright floor-to-ceiling windows act as a frame for the gorgeous bay views which are your everyday backdrop. The sensational central living and dining zone allows residents plenty of room to move, with this area serviced by the well-appointed kitchen with a moveable island bench and stainless steel appliances.
The sizeable undercover balcony is another spot to enjoy the views, with this alfresco space accessed via the main living space and one of the bedrooms. Both of the bedrooms have built-in robes, the central bathroom boasts ‘His’ and ‘Hers’ vanities, and there is a handy separate laundry.
With other additions including central heating and cooling, secure intercom, and access to Rekdek facilities incl. pool, spa, sauna, steam room, and gym, you’re close to South Wharf with restaurants and DFO Shopping, Crown Entertainment Complex, Etihad Stadium, and public transport.

Description:
Views From Every Angle in the Stunning Palladio Complex
In the sensational Palladio residential complex from renowned architect Fender Katsalidis with stunning views from all aspects to match well-appointed style this two bedroom apartment right on the NewQuay waterfront gives you unprecedented access to all the Docklands has to offer.
Wonderfully presented and awash with natural light, this 18th floor apartment defines modern and relaxed living. A comfortable living and dining zone gives you views of the harbour as well as Etihad Stadium; enjoy these calming vistas further from your undercover balcony with a wine or beer in hand.
The contemporary kitchen features stainless steel appliances, ample storage and a breakfast bar for meals on the go. Both bedrooms offer built-in robes and have easy access to the tasteful white and crisp modern bathroom. Also enjoy the convenience of a European laundry, reverse cycle heating and cooling, secure intercom, secure car space and access to a health club with rooftop pool, gym, and private function area.
While you can enjoy all the perks of this stylish Docklands retreat, the location in the popular NewQuay Precinct takes your living experience to another level. You’ll have access to an array of superb local eateries including the infamous Berth and Cargo restaurants just to name a few. You’re also near Harbour Town Shopping Centre, Melbourne Star Observation Wheel, IGA supermarket, Costco, and the free trams stops are right at your door taking you to West Preston, Bundoora RMIT, the CBD and beyond.
Insights: 1807/15 Caravel Lane, Docklands VIC 3008 was last sold in 2017 and 275 other 2 bedroom unit in Docklands have recently been sold.
